Paths¶

In [3]:
# -- PRINCIPAL PATHS -- #

study                   = 'textbook_example'

# path to study folder
path_to_study           = f'C:/rep_data3cs/data3cs/studies/{study}'

# path to config folder
path_to_config          = f'{path_to_study}/Config'

# path to rules folder
path_to_rules           = f'{path_to_config}/Rules'

# path to protocols folder
path_to_protocols       = f'{path_to_config}/Protocols'

# system state
system_state            = 'C:/rep_py3cs/py3cs/config/system/states/state_master_neutrons.json'


# -- RULES -- #

# main
"""
Applicable to crystal samples, background and Raman measurements
"""
main_rules               = f'{path_to_rules}/main_rules.json'

# qz_wl
"""
Applicable to study of excitation wavelength (no longpass filter is applied at any state)
"""
qz_wl_rules              = f'{path_to_rules}/qz_wl.json'


# -- PROTOCOLS -- #

sample_protocol          = f'{path_to_protocols}/sample.json'
bkg_protocol             = f'{path_to_protocols}/bkg.json'
qz_wl_protocol           = f'{path_to_protocols}/qz_wl.json'

# LiF
LiF_A_ROI                = sample_protocol
LiF_A_win                = 480
LiF_B_ROI                = sample_protocol
LiF_B_win                = 650

LiF_A_wl_max = 260; LiF_A_wl_min = 260; LiF_A_step = 1   # only a single exc_wl, worried about bleaching
LiF_B_wl_max = 470; LiF_B_wl_min = 430; LiF_B_step = 5 


# BaF
BaF_A_ROI                 = sample_protocol
BaF_A_win                 = 480
BaF_B_ROI                 = sample_protocol
BaF_B_win                 = 950

BaF_A_wl_max = 250; BaF_A_wl_min = 250; BaF_A_step = 1   # only a single exc_wl, worried about bleaching
BaF_B_wl_max = 340; BaF_B_wl_min = 300; BaF_B_step = 5


# -- POWER -- #

path_to_power             = f'{path_to_config}/Power/power.json' 


# -- SENSO -- #

path_to_senso             = f'{path_to_protocols}/senso.json' 



# -- VAR EXTRACTION -- #

# extract the time of a single iteration, and the total number of iterations
import json
f    = open(sample_protocol)
data = f.read()
dic  = json.loads(data)
t    = dic['times'][0][0]
its  = dic['sp_samples']
f.close()

# power correlation measurement

# check lightbeam is on pm_a
sys.ctrl(mono_wl = 500, spf = 6, source_shutter_on=True)

ask            = input('Remember to place pm_a in its place to take measurements!')
ask_again      = input('Confirm pm_a is ready measure.')

sys.ctrl(source_shutter_on=False)

path_to_save   = f'{path_to_study}/Power/power.npy'
pw             = power(path_to_power, path_to_save, main_rules)
pw.go()

(i) Electronic Baseline (EB)¶

In [6]:
filename     = f'EB_{t}'

path_to_save = f'{path_to_study}/Bkg/EB/{filename}.hdf5'

# instantiate scan object
SCAN = scan(path_to_save,
            scan_protocol_filepath = bkg_protocol,
            rule_filepath          = main_rules, 
            sys_obj                = sys
            )

SCAN.construct_hdf5()

SCAN.write_system_config()

# set the system to arbitrary wavelength
# as it does not influence the EB measurements
EB_wl = 450
sys.ctrl(mono_wl = EB_wl)

SCAN.go(EB_wl, EB_wl, 1, spec_wl_const = EB_wl, EB = True)

(ii) Room Ambience (RA)¶

In [5]:
# 480 Ambience
filename     = f'RA_{LiF_A_win}'

path_to_save = f'{path_to_study}/Bkg/RA/{filename}.hdf5'

# instantiate scan object
SCAN = scan(path_to_save,
            scan_protocol_filepath = bkg_protocol,
            rule_filepath          = main_rules, 
            sys_obj                = sys
            )

SCAN.construct_hdf5()

SCAN.write_system_config()

# set the system to excitaion wavelength
sys.apply_rules(250)
sys.ctrl(spec_wl=LiF_A_win)

SCAN.go(250, 250, 1, spec_wl_const = LiF_A_win)

# 650 Ambience
filename     = f'RA_{LiF_B_win}'

path_to_save = f'{path_to_study}/Bkg/RA/{filename}.hdf5'

# instantiate scan object
SCAN = scan(path_to_save,
            scan_protocol_filepath = bkg_protocol,
            rule_filepath          = main_rules, 
            sys_obj                = sys
            )

SCAN.construct_hdf5()

SCAN.write_system_config()

# set the system to excitaion wavelength
sys.apply_rules(450)
sys.ctrl(spec_wl=LiF_B_win)

SCAN.go(450, 450, 1, spec_wl_const = LiF_B_win)

# 950 Ambience
filename     = f'RA_{BaF_B_win}'

path_to_save = f'{path_to_study}/Bkg/RA/{filename}.hdf5'

# instantiate scan object
SCAN = scan(path_to_save,
            scan_protocol_filepath = bkg_protocol,
            rule_filepath          = main_rules, 
            sys_obj                = sys
            )

SCAN.construct_hdf5()

SCAN.write_system_config()

# set the system to excitaion wavelength
sys.apply_rules(320)
sys.ctrl(spec_wl=BaF_B_win)

SCAN.go(320, 320, 1, spec_wl_const = BaF_B_win)

# water raman

sample = 'water'

path_to_save = f'{path_to_study}/Raman/{sample}{n}.hdf5'

# instantiate scan object
SCAN = scan(path_to_save,
            scan_protocol_filepath = sample_protocol,
            rule_filepath          = main_rules, 
            sys_obj                = sys
            )

SCAN.construct_hdf5()

SCAN.write_system_config()

SCAN.go(420, 420, 1, spec_wl_const = 630)

# water raman

sample = 'water'

path_to_save = f'{path_to_study}/Raman/{sample}{n}.hdf5'

# instantiate scan object
SCAN = scan(path_to_save,
            scan_protocol_filepath = sample_protocol,
            rule_filepath          = main_rules, 
            sys_obj                = sys
            )

SCAN.construct_hdf5()

SCAN.write_system_config()

SCAN.go(420, 420, 1, spec_wl_const = 630)

# water raman

sample = 'water'

path_to_save = f'{path_to_study}/Raman/{sample}{n}.hdf5'

# instantiate scan object
SCAN = scan(path_to_save,
            scan_protocol_filepath = sample_protocol,
            rule_filepath          = main_rules, 
            sys_obj                = sys
            )

SCAN.construct_hdf5()

SCAN.write_system_config()

SCAN.go(420, 420, 1, spec_wl_const = 630)

# water raman

sample = 'water'

path_to_save = f'{path_to_study}/Raman/{sample}3.hdf5'

# instantiate scan object
SCAN = scan(path_to_save,
            scan_protocol_filepath = sample_protocol,
            rule_filepath          = main_rules, 
            sys_obj                = sys
            )

SCAN.construct_hdf5()

SCAN.write_system_config()

SCAN.go(420, 420, 1, spec_wl_const = 630)
